<h1>Configure Fanvil IP phones for VoiceTel.</h1>
<p class="lede">Fanvil's X-series desk phones (X3S, X4U, X5U, X6U, X7), V-series video phones, and H-series specialty phones all share the same SIP configuration menu. Fanvil RPS handles fleet provisioning.</p>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Web UI configuration</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Find the IP address: press <strong>Menu → Status → Network</strong>.</li>
		<li>Open <code>http://&lt;phone-ip&gt;</code>. Sign in (default <code>admin</code> / <code>admin</code> — change immediately).</li>
		<li>Open <strong>Line → SIP</strong>.</li>
		<li>Select <strong>Line 1</strong> from the line dropdown at the top.</li>
		<li>Basic Settings section:
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Line Status:</strong> Activated</li>
				<li><strong>Username:</strong> SIP username from VoiceTel onboarding</li>
				<li><strong>Display Name:</strong> caller's name</li>
				<li><strong>Authentication User:</strong> same as Username</li>
				<li><strong>Authentication Password:</strong> SIP password</li>
				<li><strong>Server Address (SIP Server 1):</strong> the SIP server host shown in your customer portal</li>
				<li><strong>Server Port:</strong> 5060</li>
				<li><strong>Transport Protocol:</strong> UDP</li>
				<li><strong>Registration Expiration:</strong> 360</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Outbound Proxy section:
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Outbound Proxy Server:</strong> same as Server Address</li>
				<li><strong>Outbound Proxy Port:</strong> 5060</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Click <strong>Apply</strong>.</li>
		<li>Open <strong>Line → SIP → Advanced Settings</strong> for the same line:
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Use STUN:</strong> No</li>
				<li><strong>Keep Alive Type:</strong> SIP Options</li>
				<li><strong>Keep Alive Period:</strong> 30</li>
				<li><strong>DTMF Type:</strong> RFC2833</li>
				<li><strong>DTMF SIP INFO Mode:</strong> Send 10/11</li>
				<li><strong>RFC2833 Payload Type:</strong> 101</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Click <strong>Apply</strong>.</li>
		<li>Open <strong>Line → Codec</strong>. Move PCMU and PCMA to the top of the enabled list. Disable codecs your VoiceTel account doesn't support.</li>
		<li>Save. The line registers within a few seconds — confirm under <strong>Status → Line</strong>.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Door phones and ATAs</h2>
	<p>Fanvil i-series door phones (i20S, i32V, i64) and ATA models use the same Line → SIP menu. Configuration is identical; the device-specific behavior (RFID, relay control, pickup-on-DTMF) is in <strong>Function Key</strong> / <strong>Output</strong> tabs and doesn't affect SIP registration.</p>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Auto-provisioning</h2>
	<p>Fanvil RPS (<code>https://rps.fanvilcloud.com</code>) is the equivalent of Yealink RPS. Register your phone's MAC range in the RPS portal and point at your VoiceTel provisioning URL. Phones boot, contact RPS, redirect, fetch config, register — no on-site touch required.</p>
	<p>Self-hosted provisioning: phones look for <code>&lt;mac&gt;.cfg</code> via HTTP/HTTPS. Contact VoiceTel engineering for a Fanvil config template.</p>
</section>

<aside class="cta-block" aria-labelledby="fanvil-cta-heading">
	<h2 id="fanvil-cta-heading">Fanvil video phone (V-series)?</h2>
	<p>V62 / V64 / V65 video phones add a video codec configuration on top of the audio config. VoiceTel engineering can advise on H.264 / VP8 codec selection if your account has video enabled.</p>
